Greek Finance Ministry Chooses Advisers for State Asset Sales

-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s   a n d   N a t a l i e   W e e k s
-- 
2011-05-18T11:19:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-18/greek-finance-ministry-chooses-advisers-for-state-asset-sales.html
Greece ’s government announced a
series of banks to advise it on state asset sales and real
estate development plans that aim to raise 50 billion euros to
pay down debt.  Nine Greek banks were retained to advise the government on
investment options for the country’s real estate holdings,
according to an e-mailed statement from the Athens-based  Finance
Ministry .  Deutsche Bank AG (DBK)  and National  Bank of Greece (TELL)  SA will
advise the government on plans to extend the concession of
gambling company  Opap SA (OPAP) , according to the statement.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Maria Petrakis at 
 mpetrakis@bloomberg.net  